actually enforced in the PM bot and identify the smallest code surface that would safely remove `19 UTC` without disturbing the rest of the strategy stack.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive.\n- The active trading hours are set directly inside `polymarket-assistant/trading_bot.py`, not in shared `src/config.py`.\n- Current live setting is:\n  - `self.active_hours = [11, 12, 19, 20]`\n- `src/config.py` contains market/indicator constants only, so the hour control is localized and low-risk to edit.\n- That means the smallest safe production change would be a one-line patch in `TradingBot.__init__`, changing the active hours from `[11, 12, 19, 20]` to `[11, 12, 20]`.\n\n**My thinking:**\nThis is good architecture news for once. The 19 UTC exclusion does not require a multi-file refactor or a new conditional branch. The control point is narrow and explicit, which means we can translate the research into a very small strategy patch when ready. That lowers implementation risk and makes the eventual change easy to reason about and revert.\n\n**Decision:**",
